## Calor-First Project

This project uses **Calor**, a DSL that compiles to C# on .NET 10. The Calor MCP server provides all compiler capabilities as tools.

### Rules for AI Agents

1. **All new code must be `.calr` files** — never create `.cs` files directly.
2. **Convert before modifying** — convert any `.cs` file to `.calr` using `calor_convert` MCP tool before making changes.
3. **Never edit `.g.cs` files** — they are auto-generated from `.calr` sources.
4. **Validate after writing** — run `calor_diagnose` MCP tool after any `.calr` edit.
5. **Look up syntax first** — use `calor_syntax_lookup` MCP tool before writing Calor code.

### MCP Tools (available via `calor mcp --stdio`)

| Category | Tools |
|----------|-------|
| **Compile & Verify** | `calor_compile`, `calor_verify`, `calor_analyze`, `calor_diagnose` |
| **Convert** | `calor_convert`, `calor_assess`, `calor_batch_convert` |
| **Navigate** | `calor_goto_definition`, `calor_find_references`, `calor_symbol_info`, `calor_document_outline`, `calor_find_symbol` |
| **Syntax** | `calor_syntax_lookup`, `calor_explain_error`, `calor_feature_support` |
| **Edit Support** | `calor_edit_preview`, `calor_impact_analysis`, `calor_lint`, `calor_format` |
| **Refinement** | `calor_obligations`, `calor_suggest_fixes`, `calor_discover_guards`, `calor_bounds_check` |

### Quick Syntax Reference

| Structure | Calor Syntax |
|-----------|-------------|
| Module | `§M{id:Name}` ... `§/M{id}` |
| Function | `§F{id:name:returnType:vis}` ... `§/F{id}` |
| Binding | `§B{name:type} expr` (immutable), `§B{~name:type}` (mutable) |
| Loop | `§L{id:var:from:to:step}` ... `§/L{id}` |
| Conditional | `§IF{id} (cond) → §R expr` |
| Contracts | `§Q (precondition)`, `§S (postcondition)` |
| Types | `i32`, `i64`, `str`, `bool`, `f64`, `void`, `?i32` (option), `i32!str` (result) |
| Expressions | Prefix notation: `(+ a b)`, `(== x 0)`, `(% i 15)` |
| Literals | `INT:42`, `STR:"hello"`, `BOOL:true`, `FLOAT:3.14` |

